result.execSummary:
The defendant Nicholas A. Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Nicholas A. Jones is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Nicholas A. Jones was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nicholas A. Jones in court with attorney Lisa A McDougal. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer M. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin.  3 cases called together:

13CF40/count 1 subject to sentencing after revocation of DPA.
15CF18/status - plea/sentencing
15CF63/status - plea/sentencing

15CF18 - prelim waived.  Colloquy on waiver.  Bindover.  Ded pleads no contest tocount 1/felony bail jumping.
15CF63 - felony is being dismissed so prelim waiver not necessary.  Def pleads no contest to count 1/operating with restricted controlled substance (w/pass.).
Court's colloquy on pleas in 15CF18 and 15CF63.

Comments by counsel.  Global resolution of the parties calls for 12 mo jail for count 1 in 13CF40; probation of 2 years with 4 months conditional jail time and costs in 15CF18 (probation and jail consecutive to 13CF40), and 2 months jail, $350 base fine ($1429 total), AODA, and 12 mo revocation in 15CF63 (jail consecutive to 13CF40 and 15CF18).

Sentence:
13CF40 - 12 months jail with work release/huber and costs.  Stayed until November 9, 2015 between 6-7 a.m.
15CF63 - 2 months or 60 days jail, consecutive to 13CF40.  $350 plus costs.  12 mo revocation.  AODA/driver safety plan.  
15CF18 - sentence withheld for 2 years with conditions of 4 months jail; attend, pay for, and succ. complete any treatment order by agent; pay costs.  Conditional time to be served consecutively to other jail sentence.  Probation also to begin consecutive to the jail in 13CF40.

Submit DNA sample today at the Richland County Jail.  Def will need to sign up however probation wants that to happen.

Court provides felony firearm admonishments.

Court remits felony DNA surcharge on 15CF18 but keeps on the others.

Count 2 in 15CF63 and count 2 on 15CF18 both dismissed.
